abstract_ssm: This collection consists of one ledger, dated 1874 to 1915 and  contains a membership roll of the Trinity Baptist Church, listing member names, baptism dates, dates of acceptance to and dismissal from the church, and member addresses.  Trinity Baptist Church was established in 1875. During the church's first two years, congregants met at Ridgewood Hall on Broadway in the Bedford-Stuyvesant neighborhood of Brooklyn.
